4.

Get the word index and then Create a key-value pair for word and word_id

In [13]:
word_index = imdb.get_word_index()
In [14]:
reverse_word_map = dict(map(reversed, word_index.items()))
In [15]:
# Function takes a tokenized sentence and returns the words
def sequence_to_text(list_of_indices):
    # Looking up words in dictionary
    words = [reverse_word_map.get(letter) for letter in list_of_indices]
    return(words)

In [17]:
from keras.datasets import imdb
from keras.models import Sequential
from keras.layers import Dense
from keras.layers import Embedding
from keras.preprocessing import sequence
from keras.layers import LSTM
In [18]:
### create the model
model = Sequential()
model.add(Embedding(vocab_size, 128, trainable=True, input_length=maxlen))
model.add(LSTM(units=64, dropout=0.2))
model.add(Dense(32, activation='relu'))
model.add(Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))
model.compile(loss='binary_crossentropy', optimizer='adam', metrics=['accuracy'])
model.summary()
### Fit the model
model.fit(x_train, y_train, validation_data=(x_test, y_test), epochs=10, batch_size=500, verbose=1)

import re
from nltk.corpus import stopwords
In [48]:
def clean_text(text, remove_stopwords=True):
  # Convert words to lower case
  text = text.lower()
  if True:
    text = text.split()
    new_text = []
    for word in text:
      if word in contractions:
        new_text.append(contractions[word])
      else:
        new_text.append(word)
      text = " ".join(new_text)
      text = re.sub(r'https?:\/\/.*[\r\n]*', '', text, flags=re.MULTILINE)
      text = re.sub(r'\<a href', ' ', text)
      text = re.sub(r'&amp;', '', text)
      text = re.sub(r'[_"\-;%()|+&=*%.,!?:#$@\[\]/]', ' ', text)
      text = re.sub(r'<br />', ' ', text)
      text = re.sub(r'\'', ' ', text)
      if remove_stopwords:
        text = text.split()
        stops = set(stopwords.words("english"))
        text = [w for w in text if not w in stops]
        text = " ".join(text)
  return text

In [66]:
EMBEDDING_FILE = 'glove.6B/glove.6B.200d.txt'

embeddings = {}
for o in open(EMBEDDING_FILE):
    word = o.split(" ")[0]
    # print(word)
    embd = o.split(" ")[1:]
    embd = np.asarray(embd, dtype='float32')
    # print(embd)
    embeddings[word] = embd

creating weight matrix

In [68]:
embedding_matrix = np.zeros((vocab_size, 200))

for word, i in tokenizer.word_index.items():
    embedding_vector = embeddings.get(word)
    if embedding_vector is not None:
        embedding_matrix[i] = embedding_vector

len(embeddings.values())
Out[68]:
400000

Creating Bidirectional LSTM Model

In [69]:
model = Sequential()

model.add(Embedding(vocab_size, embedding_size, weights = [embedding_matrix]))
### Bidirectional LSTM layer 
model.add(Bidirectional(LSTM(512, return_sequences = True)))
### dense
model.add(Dense(256, activation='relu'))
##dropout
model.add(Dropout(0.2, input_shape=(256,)))
##sigmoid
model.add(Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))
model.compile(loss='binary_crossentropy', optimizer='adam', metrics=['accuracy'])
model.summary()
